NAME: APPLICATION
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of application being modeled

DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of process being modeled

NAME: SUBPROCESS
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of subprocess being modeled

NAME: ALPHA
DESCRIPTION: Controls weighting of upstream values in advection approximations when :envvar:`IORDER` = 1

NAME: ALPHA_SWAT
DESCRIPTION: Controls weighting of upstream values in advection approximations in the shallow water model when :envvar:`IORDER_SWAT` = 1

NAME: DTIMPX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum Courant number used to limit the time step size in the implicit advection model, :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1. Used in addition to any other limiting factors.

NAME: IFENRG
DESCRIPTION: Flag for internal energy evaluation

NAME: IFPK
DESCRIPTION: Flag for F-packing

NAME: IFRHO
DESCRIPTION: Flag for density evaluation

NAME: IFTHEXP
DESCRIPTION: Thermal expansion flag for flow with density a function of temperature

NAME: IFVOF
DESCRIPTION: Flag for F advection options

NAME: IFSLP
DESCRIPTION: Flag for two-fluid interface velocity slip option

NAME: IMPADV
DESCRIPTION: Advection explicit/implicit flag

NAME: IMPADV2
DESCRIPTION: Time step control flag for implicit advection option, :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1

NAME: IORDER

NAME: IBM

NAME: IBM_PROBE_DIRECTION_METHOD

NAME: DT_THRESH
DESCRIPTION: Time step threshold for implicit advection. Cells with local advective stability limit below :envvar:`DT_THRESH` are treated implicitly. Used when :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1 and :envvar:`IMPADV2` = 2.

NAME: V_THRESH
DESCRIPTION: Velocity threshold for implicit advection. Cells with velocity above :envvar:`V_THRESH` are treated implicitly. Used when :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1 and :envvar:`IMPADV2` = 1.

NAME: IF_VOL_CORR
DESCRIPTION: Flag for fluid #1 volume correction model. Only applied to one-fluid with free-surface and two-fluid problems to maintain fluid #1 volume conservation.

NAME: IVOL_CORR_TIME
DESCRIPTION: Flag for the definition of the characteristic time for volume correction :envvar:`VOL_CORR_TIME`

NAME: VOL_CORR_TIME
DESCRIPTION: Characteristic time for fluid #1 volume correction. Defaults to 10.0 when :envvar:`IVOL_CORR_TIME` = 1. Must be positive when :envvar:`IVOL_CORR_TIME` = 2.

NAME: ICLID
DESCRIPTION: Flag for the collision model. Only applied to the coupled-motion GMO components

NAME: FRCMOB
DESCRIPTION: Global coefficient of friction during collision between coupled-motion GMO components and other components and walls

NAME: STRNGMOB
DESCRIPTION: Global coefficient of Stronge's restitution during collision between coupled-motion GMO components and other components and walls. Values should be between 0.0 and 1.0.

NAME: ITETTSE
DESCRIPTION: Flag to use tetrahedral meshing to generate the mesh of the solidified fluid region of the thermal stress evolution model. Default is hexahedral meshes, and this value is overridden when reading in an existing mesh from a file (see :envvar:`IFFEMF` in :ref:`namelistXPUTFileControlOptions`).

NAME: ICPLTSE
DESCRIPTION: Flag to control coupling between the solidified fluid region (the Thermal Stress Evolution region) and neighboring Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) components (see :envvar:`IFSI(m)` in :ref:`ComponentPropertiesFluidStructureInteractionFSImodel`). Default is only basic constraining/non-constraining behavior between the TSE region and neighboring FSI components (see :envvar:`IFSOFT(m)` in :ref:`ComponentPropertiesThermalStressEvolutionTSEModel`).

NAME: FRCTTSE
DESCRIPTION: Friction coefficient between Thermal Stress Evolution (TSE) region and neighboring Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) components. A negative value indicates that the coefficient is infinite (i.e., tangential traction is not limited), and a positive value indicates the friction coefficient. Its value represents the ratio between the limit of the magnitude of tangential traction to the normal traction between the TSE region and the component face. Physical values are typically less than 1.0.

NAME: IGMRES
DESCRIPTION: Pressure iteration option

NAME: IOPT_GMRES
DESCRIPTION: Convergence criterion for the GMRES pressure solver. The GMRES pressure solver uses two types of convergence criteria. The absolute convergence criterion (v11.1 and earlier) uses a simple absolute convergence limit for the residual. The hybrid convergence criterion (v11.2 and later) uses a combination of absolute and relative convergence limits. The hybrid convergence criterion is more generic and accurate. However, because it often iterates more, it may be computationally more expensive for some problems.

NAME: IPUN
DESCRIPTION: Uniform pressure adjustment for compressible flows (if :envvar:`IPUN` = 0, there is no adjustment; if :envvar:`IPUN` = 1 adjust the pressure once at the end of each cycle).

DESCRIPTION: FAVOR |TM| volume adjustment for stability with larger time-step limit (see :envvar:`AVRCK`)

NAME: AVRCK
DESCRIPTION: Cell volume fractions are adjusted in so-called *sliver* cells so that the area/volume fraction ratios do not exceed this value.

NAME: TOLERANCE_GAP
DESCRIPTION: Gap size tolerance. Gaps that are smaller than the tolerance will be closed.

NAME: TOLERANCE_SKIN
DESCRIPTION: Skin size tolerance. Skins that are smaller than the tolerance will be converted to the base component which they

NAME: CCOLOR
DESCRIPTION: Component :envvar:`m` RGB color value for display in the Graphical User Interface

NAME: IFCOMPENABLED
DESCRIPTION: Activation flag for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: IFRCO
DESCRIPTION: Flag for force and torque output for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: IFWETAR
DESCRIPTION: Flag for wetted area output for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: IFOB
DESCRIPTION: "Free" (or phantom) component flag

NAME: IPREF
DESCRIPTION: Flag for reference pressure for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: IMO
DESCRIPTION: Type of component :envvar:`m`

NAME: MATERIAL
DESCRIPTION: Character string allowing user to identify the material of component :envvar:`m` (up to 256 characters).

NAME: NOBR
DIMENSIONS: Component identifier for restarts; used to identify the old component number if components have been changed for restart runs.

NAME: NOBS
DESCRIPTION: Number of components

NAME: OBSID
DESCRIPTION: Character string allowing user to identify component :envvar:`m` (up to 30 characters)

NAME: SUBCMPID
DESCRIPTION: Character string allowing user to identify subcomponent :envvar:`n` (up to 50 characters)

NAME: XFRCO
DESCRIPTION: x coordinate of the reference point for torque evaluation for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: YFRCO
DESCRIPTION: y coordinate of the reference point for torque evaluation for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: ZFRCO
DESCRIPTION: z coordinate of the reference point for torque evaluation for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: IGEN
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent generation flag, indicates source of geometric data for region :envvar:`n`

NAME: IFSUBCOMPENABLED
DESCRIPTION: Activation flag for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: IOB
DESCRIPTION: Associates subcomponent :envvar:`n` with a particular component

NAME: IOH
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent type

NAME: FSTL
DESCRIPTION: File name for stereolithography (STL) CAD data file, where "nn "= n.

NAME: FTOPO
DESCRIPTION: File name for raster file format data file, where "nn "= n.

NAME: ANGLH
DESCRIPTION: Upper cylindrical angle limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n` (measured in the x-y plane from the x-axis, in degrees).

NAME: ANGLL
DESCRIPTION: Lower cylindrical angle limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n` (measured in the x-y plane from the x-axis, in degrees).

NAME: CONEH
DESCRIPTION: Upper conical angle limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n` (measured from the z-axis in degrees).

NAME: CONEL
DESCRIPTION: Lower conical angle limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n` (measured from the z-axis in degrees).

NAME: RAH
DESCRIPTION: Upper cylindrical-radius limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: RAL
DESCRIPTION: Lower cylindrical-radius limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: RSH
DESCRIPTION: Upper spherical-radius limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: RSL
DESCRIPTION: Lower spherical-radius limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: RTORIN
DESCRIPTION: Minor toroid radius

NAME: RTOROUT
DESCRIPTION: Major toroid radius

NAME: XH
DESCRIPTION: Upper x-coordinate limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: XL
DESCRIPTION: Lower x-coordinate limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: YL
DESCRIPTION: Lower y-coordinate limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZH
DESCRIPTION: Upper z-coordinate limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZL
DESCRIPTION: Lower z-coordinate limit for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: NODATRPLC
DESCRIPTION: Elevation to replace *NODAT* value from raster format data files for subcomponent :envvar:`n`.

NAME: CC
DESCRIPTION: Function constant coefficient for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CX
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`x` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CY
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`y` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CZ
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`z` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CXY
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`xy` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CXZ
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`xz` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CYZ
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`yz` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CX2
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`x^2` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CY2
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`y^2` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CZ2
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`z^2` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CRXY
DESCRIPTION: Function coefficient of :math:`\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}` for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CDUM
DESCRIPTION: Dummy function coefficient for subcomponent :envvar:`n` for customizing functions.

NAME: MAGN
DESCRIPTION: Magnification (scaling) factor for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: MAGNX
DESCRIPTION: Scaling factor in x-direction for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: MAGNY
DESCRIPTION: Scaling factor in y-direction for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: MAGNZ
DESCRIPTION: Scaling factor in z-direction for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: ROTX
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent :envvar:`n` rotation about x-axis in degrees, positive in right hand sense

NAME: ROTY
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent :envvar:`n` rotation about y-axis in degrees

NAME: ROTZ
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent :envvar:`n` rotation about z-axis in degrees

NAME: TRNX
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent :envvar:`n` translation in x-direction

NAME: TRNY
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent :envvar:`n` translation in y-direction

NAME: TRNZ
DESCRIPTION: Subcomponent :envvar:`n` translation in z-direction

NAME: XTRFC
DESCRIPTION: x-coordinate of transformation center for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: YTRFC
DESCRIPTION: y-coordinate of transformation center for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: ZTRFC
DESCRIPTION: z-coordinate of transformation center for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: IVR
DESCRIPTION: Cooling channel activation flag for subcomponent :envvar:`n`

NAME: CCTIME
DESCRIPTION: Time table for the time dependent properties of the cooling channel

NAME: CCTEMP
DESCRIPTION: Temperature of the cooling channel between time :envvar:`CCTIME(t,n)` and :envvar:`CCTIME(t+1,n)`

NAME: FCCTEMP
DESCRIPTION: The external filename for tabular temperature of the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` as a function of time (used only if :envvar:`ICCTEMPC(n)` :math:`\geq` 2)

NAME: ICCTEMPC
DESCRIPTION: The column number for temperature of the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` in the external file

NAME: HCCT
DESCRIPTION: Heat transfer coefficient between the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` and its component :envvar:`m` between time :envvar:`CCTIME(t,n)` and :envvar:`CCTIME(t+1,n)`

NAME: FHCCT
DESCRIPTION: The external filename for tabular heat transfer coefficient between the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` and its component :envvar:`m` as a function of time (used only if :envvar:`IHCCTC(n)` :math:`\geq` 2)

NAME: IHCCTC
DESCRIPTION: The column number for heat transfer coefficient between the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` and its component :envvar:`m` in the external file

NAME: ICCCONTROL
DESCRIPTION: On/off control mode for the cooling channel

NAME: ICCTIME
DESCRIPTION: On/off status for the cooling channel

NAME: FICCTIME
DESCRIPTION: The external filename for tabular on/off status for the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` as a function of time (used only if :envvar:`ICCTIME(n)` :math:`\geq` 2)

NAME: IICCTIMEC
DESCRIPTION: The column number for on/off status for the cooling channel subcomponent :envvar:`n` in the external file

NAME: ICCPRB
DESCRIPTION: Probe number controlling the on/off status of the cooling channel

NAME: CCTC1
DESCRIPTION: Turn-on temperature at probe :envvar:`ICCPRB(n)` for the cooling channel

NAME: CCTC2
DESCRIPTION: Turn-off temperature at probe :envvar:`ICCPRB(n)` for the cooling channel

NAME: CCHEAT
DESCRIPTION: Critical total heat to turn off the cooling channel

NAME: IGTRFMVB
DESCRIPTION: Flag to apply component transformations to the body-fixed coordinate system for GMO component :envvar:`m`.

NAME: GMAGN
DESCRIPTION: Magnification (scaling) factor for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: GROTX
DESCRIPTION: Rotation of component :envvar:`m` about x-axis, positive in right hand

NAME: GROTY
DESCRIPTION: Rotation of component :envvar:`m` about y-axis, positive in right hand

NAME: GROTZ
DESCRIPTION: Rotation of component :envvar:`m` about z-axis, positive in right hand

NAME: GTRNX
DESCRIPTION: Translation of component :envvar:`m` in x-direction

NAME: GTRNY
DESCRIPTION: Translation of component :envvar:`m` in y-direction

NAME: GTRNZ
DESCRIPTION: Translation of component :envvar:`m` in z-direction

NAME: GXTRFC
DESCRIPTION: x-coordinate of transformation center for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: GYTRFC
DESCRIPTION: y-coordinate of transformation center for component :envvar:`m`

NAME: GZTRFC
DESCRIPTION: z-coordinate of transformation center for component :envvar:`m`
